opening_comment: The entire Exclusive Economic Zone of Peru seems to be added to the Peru relation, instead of just the territorial waters.
closing_comment: Hello A67-A67 The Peruvian sea[0] is a bit different from other countries, because Peru is one of the few countries in the world that has not signed the Law of the Sea Convention[1]. In addition the Political Constitution of Peru in article 54[2] considers 200 nauticas miles as part of its territory. [0] https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mar_de_Grau [1] https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Nations_Convention_on_the_Law_of_the_Sea#Parties [2] http://www.congreso.gob.pe/Docs/files/CONSTITUTION_27_11_2012_ENG.pdf Regards Omar
